Ruskin (1903), ^Inf~. 3.1                         Doc 2 of 4, Screen  1

Thus the fatal inscription on the Hades gate is written in `obscure colour'    
[line 10], and the air which torments the passionate spirits is `aer nero,'    
^black~ air (Inferno, v. 51), called presently afterward (line 86) malignant   
air, just as the grey cliffs are called malignant cliffs [^Inf.~  vii.  108].  
                                                                               
     ^Modern Painters~, vol. iii. ch. xv. sec. 9.                              
                                                                               
                                                                               
                                                                               
                                                                               
                                                                               
                                                                               
                                                                               
                                                                               
                                                                               
                                                                               
                                                                               
                                                                               
